# {{ hostname }} Node App

This scaffold is a minimal production-oriented Node service for `{{ hostname }}`.

## Files

- `docker-compose.yml`: Traefik-connected app service
- `Dockerfile`: container build for the app
- `package.json`: minimal Node package metadata
- `src/server.js`: simple HTTP server that listens on `PORT`
- `.env.example`: starter environment values

## Local adjustments

1. Copy `.env.example` to `.env` only if you need to change the default port or hostname values.
2. Build and start the stack with `docker compose up --build`.
3. Verify the container becomes healthy and that `https://{{ hostname }}/` returns the scaffold JSON response.
4. Replace `src/server.js` with your real application code when ready.
5. Add any dependencies you need to `package.json`.

## Runtime behavior

The default server responds on `/` with JSON containing:

- `hostname`
- `appHostname`
- `nodeEnv`
- `requestPath`

Traefik forwards `{{ hostname }}` to the app on port `3000`.
The generated compose service also includes a container healthcheck against `http://127.0.0.1:${PORT:-3000}/healthz`.
